Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reportCritTerm(25.10)                                    reportCritTerm(25.10)

Name
       reportCritTerm  -  Performs  slack analysis and writes the names of all
       critical terminals to the specified file

Syntax
       reportCritTerm

       [-help]

       -outfile <fileName>

       Performs slack analysis and writes the names of all critical  terminals
       to the specified file. As a result, deterioration of setup slack can be
       avoided while the Innovus software repairs hold time violations.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each reportCritTerm parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man reportCritTerm

       -outfile <fileName>
              Specifies the name of report file.

Command Order
       Use  this  command after the timing graph is built by timeDesign/optDe-
       sign.

Example
              * The following commands write the setup critical terminals into
                a file called critTerm:

                setAnalysisMode -checkType setup

                reportCritTerm -outfile critTerm

Related Information
              * optDesign

              * setOptMode

              * timeDesign

